themeMusic.name: AJ Styles
themeMusic.details: During his recent run in New Japan Pro Wrestling, A.J. Styles became the first non-Japanese wrestler to win the IWGP heavyweight title since Brock Lesnar back in 2005

themeMusic.name: Andre the Giant
themeMusic.details: His size was a result of gigantism caused by excess growth hormone, which later resulted in acromegaly. It also led to his being called "The Eighth Wonder of the World"

themeMusic.name: A-Train / Prince Albert
themeMusic.brief: Real name : Matt Bloom , Hometown : Orlando, Florida,United States
themeMusic.details: He was a star football player at the University of Pittsburgh, had a brief NFL career, and then became a schoolteacher before quitting to follow a lifelong wrestling dream.

themeMusic.name: Batista
themeMusic.details: Batista held several jobs in his early adulthood - as Bouncer, Bodybuilder and Lifeguard.

themeMusic.name: The Big Show
themeMusic.brief: Known as the world's largest athlete.
themeMusic.details: Big Show played basketball while he was in high school, junior college, and university. His average in high school was more than 32 points, with a whopping 20 rebounds and 11 blocks average per game.

themeMusic.name: Bob Backlund
themeMusic.details: He attended Waldorf Junior College, where he was an All-American in both wrestling and football.

themeMusic.name: Bobby Lashley
themeMusic.details: He is The First African-American ECW Champion.

themeMusic.name: Boogey Man
themeMusic.details: He was titled Rookie of the Year (2006)

themeMusic.name: Booker-T
themeMusic.brief: Finishing move : Book End   Hometown : Texas City
themeMusic.details: Booker-T is the first non-mixed race African American to become a world champion in WWE,and was voted the greatest World Heavyweight Champion in a WWE viewer poll.

themeMusic.name: Bray Wyatt
themeMusic.details: Apart from Cena and Austin, Bray is another name who used the Stunner. And he did not use it for a filler move; he used it as a finisher. This happened back during his Axel Mulligan days.

themeMusic.name: Bret the Hitman Hart
themeMusic.details: Sunglasses became a part of Harts iconic look, but the reason he initially decided to don them was due to a lack of confidence when he was starting out. Hart noticed in a promo, which never made it to air due to technical issues, that his eyes made him look nervous and decided to shield them with sunglasses

themeMusic.name: The British Bulldog
themeMusic.brief: From Manchester, England - Real name : David Smith
themeMusic.details: He was the inaugural WWF European Champion and holds the records for longest single reign (206 days) and total days as champion.

themeMusic.name: Brock Lesnar
themeMusic.details: Lesnar has never lost to The Undertaker when they have been the main event for PPV. The world was shocked when he beat The Deadman at WrestleMania XXX and The Undertaker has never gotten his revenge.

themeMusic.name: Carlito
themeMusic.brief: Finishing move : Backstabber  Origin : The Caribbean
themeMusic.details: Carlito made his debut on the main event of SmackDown! as Carlito Caribbean Cool. He is the only wrestler to win a championship on two separate debuts in WWE and the second Puerto Rican to become Intercontinental Champion after Pedro Morales

themeMusic.name: Chris Benoit'
themeMusic.details: Toothless aggression’ is a phrase that is closely associated with BenoitThe tooth actually popped out while Benoit was playing with his pet Rottweiler.

themeMusic.name: Chris Jericho
themeMusic.details: Chris is a man of many talents that extend beyond the ring. Not only is he a WWE Superstar, but he is also the lead singer of a rock band named Fozzy.

themeMusic.name: Christian
themeMusic.details: Taking inspiration from the biggest star of the nineties, the future Captain Charisma found his name. The Christian name comes from Christian Slater, star of True Romance

themeMusic.name: CM Punk
themeMusic.brief: Finisher : Go to Sleep - The voice of the Voiceless
themeMusic.details: CM stands for chick magnet. So, his name is ‘Chick Magnet Punk.’

themeMusic.name: Daniel Bryan
themeMusic.details: Daniel Bryan is an environmentalist does his best to live as green as possible and is a huge proponent of solar panel use and sustainable living.

themeMusic.name: Kevin Nash (Diesel)
themeMusic.details: Nash's 358-day WWF Championship reign is the longest of the 1990s.In WCW, Nash became the first wrestler to defeat Goldberg and in the process ended his undefeated streak of 173–0 at Starrcade in 1998.

themeMusic.name: Dolph Ziggler
themeMusic.details: He is named after his great-grandfather Dolph. The name means “Noble wolf” in Swedish. The last name, Ziggler, came from his friends and he liked it so much it stuck.

themeMusic.name: The Dudley Boyz
themeMusic.details: They are The Only Tag Team To Have Held The 7 Major Championships.

themeMusic.name: DX
themeMusic.brief: Gang of rebels founded by HBK and Triple-H
themeMusic.details: Bret Hart "Named" D-Generation X.During one of Bret Hart`s promos directed at Shawn and Triple H, he told them "You`re nothing but a couple of degenerates."

themeMusic.name: Eddie Guerrero
themeMusic.details: Eddie once wore a mask When Eddie first started out wrestling, it was under the ring name ‘Mascara Magica’ in the CMLL foundation.

themeMusic.name: Edge
themeMusic.details: One of the most decorated superstars of all time.He is the only wrestler in history to win a King of the ring tournament,Money in the bank ladder match and a royal rumble match.

themeMusic.name: Evolution
themeMusic.brief: The villainous stable was a part of WWE`s Raw brand between 2003 and 2005 and during 2007 and 2014.
themeMusic.details: The stable catapulted Randy Orton and Batista`s career.14 years on, the pair have won 17 world titles between them, four Royal Rumbles and headlined multiple WrestleManias, including together alongside Daniel Bryan in 2014.

themeMusic.name: Four Horsemen
themeMusic.brief: The original members of the stable were Ric Flair, Arn Anderson, Tully Blanchard, and Ole Anderson.
themeMusic.details: Unlike The Bullet Club or the nWo, The Four Horsemen required more than a pulse to be a member. Being a Horsemen meant that you were the best the business had to offer. It was a tight knit group and being a Horsemen was an achievement and an honor.

themeMusic.name: Bill Goldberg
themeMusic.details: While Goldberg was playing for the Atlanta Falcons, he used to be a member of a gym that was owned by Sting and Lex Luger. In an interview with Sports Illustrated, Goldberg credits Sting with changing his mind about the wrestling business.

themeMusic.name: The Hardy Boyz
themeMusic.brief: Real life brothers as Billed from Cameron, North Carolina, U.S.
themeMusic.details: Long before their days in the WWE, the Hardy brothers were huge wrestling fans as youngsters and started their own backyard wrestling promotion with their friends called Trampoline Championship Wrestling

themeMusic.name: Hulk Hogan
themeMusic.details: In 1985 Hulk faced the worst fear of superstitious athletes everywhere by appearing on the cover of Sports Illustrated, becoming the first wrestler to ever grace the front of the iconic magazine.

themeMusic.name: The Hurricane
themeMusic.brief: Finisher : Vertebreaker  , Hometown : Smithfield, North Carolina
themeMusic.details: He was a two-time Cruiserweight Champion, a European Champion and Hardcore Champion during his time in the WWE.

themeMusic.name: Iron Sheik
themeMusic.details: It turns out that Sheik made Rock aware of "jabroni" early in his career, when the two were on a flight together. Rock took to the word quickly and he worked it into his regular routine.

themeMusic.name: Jack Swagger
themeMusic.brief: Finishing move : Patriot Lock   Hometown : Perry,Oklahoma'
themeMusic.details: Jack swagger played two sports at the University of Oklahoma before focusing on wrestling. He was an All American as a heavyweight his senior year, recording 30 pins.

themeMusic.name: Jeff Hardy
themeMusic.details: Hardy is still acknowledged for his initial work during his first run with WWE and is best known for his daredevil series of TLC matches.Hardy is involved in motocross, music, painting and other artistic endeavors. He is currently a member of the band PeroxWhy?Gen

themeMusic.name: John Cena
themeMusic.details: This may come as no surprise to some, but John Cena holds the world record for Make-A-Wish Foundation wishes granted, with over 500 – more than double what the next runner-ups have.

themeMusic.name: John Morrison - Johnny Nitro
themeMusic.details: Morrisons first contact WWE came when he auditioned for the second series of Tough Enough, but he failed to make it through to the final process the main reason was that Kevin Dunn found him to be too much of a showoff, despite the praise of other judges including Jim Ross.

themeMusic.name: Kane
themeMusic.brief: One half of the brothers of destruction.
themeMusic.details: In WWE, Kane is a three-time world champion and a 12-time world tag team champion.Kane holds the record for cumulative Royal Rumble match eliminations at 44.

themeMusic.name: Kofi Kingston
themeMusic.brief: Finisher : S.O.S, Trouble in Paradise Hometown :  GHANA
themeMusic.details: Kofi credits his training in the martial art "Capoeira" for his kick-based offense in the ring. Capoeira requires a lot of agility in order to take out opponents with various spin kicks while distracting them with flips.

themeMusic.name: Kurt Angle
themeMusic.details: After winning gold at the summer Olympics in 1996, Kurt considered joining UFC. UFC offered him a deal which consisted of 10 fights and $150,000, which he rejected because he thought the risks involved in fighting were not worth it.

themeMusic.name: Mark Henry
themeMusic.brief: Finishing move : The Worlds Strongest Slam
themeMusic.details: He is a two-time Olympian and a gold, silver, and bronze medalist at the Pan American Games in 1995.As a powerlifter, he was WDFPF World Champion (1995) and a two-time U.S. National Champion as well as an all-time raw world record holder in the squat and deadlift.

themeMusic.name: Matt Hardy
themeMusic.details: In high school, Matt was an excellent student. His grades made him eligible for many prestigious schools and awards, but he simply wasnt motivated and didnt apply himself to the level he shouldve. In his senior year, he was nominated for the Morehead Award, considered to be the most prestigious scholarship in the state of North Carolina.

themeMusic.name: Mick Foley
themeMusic.details: He Is A Three-Time New York Times Best Selling Author

themeMusic.name: Mr. Perfect
themeMusic.brief: Father of current WWE wrestler Curtis Axel
themeMusic.details: WCW recognized Hennig as "one of the best all-round competitors this [wrestling] business has ever produced", while WWE credited him for raising the accepted standard of technical wrestling.He was inducted into the WWE Hall of Fame in 2007.

themeMusic.name: Nation of Domination
themeMusic.brief: The Rock was a part of this Stable
themeMusic.details: The nation of Domination had few title runs.Thankfully with Faarooq and the Godfather, the Nation now has two members in the Hall of Fame

themeMusic.name: The New Day
themeMusic.details: On December 14, 2016, they became the longest reigning tag team champions in WWE history (beating Demolition`s 28-year-old record of 478 days with WWE`s original World Tag Team Championship)

themeMusic.name: Nexus
themeMusic.brief: A professional wrestling stable in WWE that competed on the Raw brand originally consisting of eight rookies of NXT season one.
themeMusic.details: The Nexus originally debuted shortly after the first season of NXT during it`s game show era. It included Wade Barrett, Skip Sheffield, Darren Young, Heath Slater, Michael Tarver, David Otunga, Justin Gabriel and Daniel Bryan. Bryan was kicked out of the group early on due to a real firing from WWE.

themeMusic.name: NWO
themeMusic.brief: It is a professional wrestling stable that originally consisted of "Hollywood" Hulk Hogan, Scott Hall and Kevin Nash.
themeMusic.details: Nash And Hogan Own Half Of NWO Merchandise Rights

themeMusic.name: Owen Hart
themeMusic.brief: Finisher : Bridging Northern Lights suplex , Sharpshooter
themeMusic.details: He was the 1994 WWF King of the Ring.

themeMusic.name: Papa Shango / The Godfather
themeMusic.brief: Ring name: The Godfather & finisher : Inverted shoulder breaker
themeMusic.details: Wright is a two-time USWA Unified World Heavyweight Champion, a one-time WWF Intercontinental Champion, and a one-time WWF Tag Team Champion (with Bull Buchanan)

themeMusic.name: Randy Orton
themeMusic.details: After his discharge from the marines, Ortons began refereeing for World Organized Wrestling.Mere months later he landed a contract with WWE.

themeMusic.name: Randy Savage (Macho Man)
themeMusic.details: Savage was drafted by the St.Louis Cardinals in the early 1970s and he spent five years playing in the minor leagues.

themeMusic.name: Rey Mysterio
themeMusic.brief: Finishing move : 619   Hometown : Chula Vista, California
themeMusic.details: Mysterio released a song called ‘Booyaka 619’ in 2005, and he performed it during his entrance to the ring with rapper Madd One.

themeMusic.name: Ric Flair
themeMusic.details: Ric Flairs holds the record for winning the most wrestling World Heavyweight Championships

themeMusic.name: Rikishi
themeMusic.details: In 1996, Rikishi gimmicked as The Sultan. He was masked and never spoke supposably because his tongue had been cut out.

themeMusic.name: Road Dogg
themeMusic.brief: Was once a member of the group DX and New age outlaws
themeMusic.details: James (Real name) served in the United States Marine Corps. His tenure lasted from 1987 to 1993 and he fought in Operation Desert Storm in 1991, where he was a platoon sergeant in command of thirty-three Marines

themeMusic.name: Rob Van Dam
themeMusic.brief: Moves : Rolling Thunder , Finisher : Five star Frog Splash
themeMusic.details: In 2002, Van Dam was ranked the number one wrestler in the world by Pro Wrestling Illustrated. He was voted “Most Popular Wrestler” by readers of the magazine in 2001 and again in 2002.

themeMusic.name: Rowdy Roddy Piper
themeMusic.details: Perhaps the most infamous moment of Piper’s career was when he smashed a (real) coconut over the head of Jimmy Snuka on the set of Piper’s Pit, which legitimately hurt snuka

themeMusic.name: Roman Reigns
themeMusic.brief: The Samoan member of the Shield
themeMusic.details: Reigns is a part of the same famous wrestling family that The Rock is. In the 2014 Royal Rumble Reigns made a new record by eliminating 12 opponents before he was finally eliminated.

themeMusic.name: Santino Marella
themeMusic.details: one of his biggest goals in doing what he does as Santino Marella is to get a reaction out of his fellow wrestlers and Divas. When he's involved in promos or segments with other people, he intentionally sets out to have them break character and laugh, or at least smile, at his antics.

themeMusic.name: Scott Hall
themeMusic.brief: Former member of the New World Order - NWO
themeMusic.details: Scott Hall spent his high school years in Munich, Germany before he began wrestling in Germany, Japan and Puerto Rico.

themeMusic.name: Scott Steiner
themeMusic.details: Steiner is a decorated tag team wrestler. During the 80s and 90s he wrestled alongside his older brother Rick as The Steiner Brothers, being considered one of the best tag teams of all time.

themeMusic.name: Scotty 2 Hotty
themeMusic.brief: Finishing move : The Worm , Hometown : Orlando, Florida
themeMusic.details: In February 2013, Garland began training as a firefighter. In June 2013, he graduated from the Lake Tech Fire Academy in Florida

themeMusic.name: Sgt. Slaughter
themeMusic.details: Before he became the most feared man in any communist regime, Sarge went by his given name of Robert Remus. Unlike Captain Lou Albano, Remus actually earned his wrestling nickname as a Marine Corps drill sergeant on Parris Island. Presumably, this is where he learned to call people maggots

themeMusic.name: Shane McMahon
themeMusic.details: McMahon is a fourth generation wrestling promoter as a member of the McMahon family.Known for his high-risk moves, he won the European Championship once and the Hardcore Championship once.

themeMusic.name: Shawn Michaels - HBK
themeMusic.details: Shawn knew he wanted to be a professional wrestler at the age of 12 and even performed a routine in his high schools talent show, complete with fake blood.

themeMusic.name: Sheamus
themeMusic.details: From 1999-2007 Sheamus worked for a few different IT companies including Symantec and Hartford Life in Dublin. While working his IT jobs he made CAT-5 cables and used Ghost to image machines.

themeMusic.name: Shelton Benjamin
themeMusic.details: Shelton Benjamin is one of the best pure athletes in the history of the WWE. He was a high school heavyweight wrestling champion. He later became a two-time All American at the University of Minnesota.

themeMusic.name: Shinsuke Nakamura
themeMusic.details: He Was The Youngest IWGP Heavyweight Champion In History and also had a short, successful MMA career

themeMusic.name: sting
themeMusic.details: Prior to signing with WWE, the promotion referred to Sting as the greatest wrestler to never wrestle for them. WWE also called Sting the greatest superstar in WCW history before he eventually signing with the promotion in 2014.

themeMusic.name: Stone Cold Steve Austin
themeMusic.details: Vince McMahon said that when it came to addressing box office drawing power, Austin was the most profitable wrestler in the history of the WWE.Hes held 21 championships throughout his wrestling career.

themeMusic.name: Tajiri
themeMusic.brief: Known for spitting Green mist thereby blinding his opponent. Origin : Japan
themeMusic.details: Tajiri initially wanted to be a kickboxer and was training for it.It was the lucha libre of Mexico that eventually convinced him to enter the Animal Hamaguchi Wrestling Gym

themeMusic.name: Test
themeMusic.details: Ranked No. 37 of the 500 top singles wrestlers of the year in the PWI 500 in 2001

themeMusic.name: The Rock
themeMusic.details: WWE Smackdown! is named after The Rocks catchphrase "layeth the smackdown.The played theme is the Rocks hollywood theme.

themeMusic.name: Triple H
themeMusic.details: His total of 14 world championships is the third-most all-time (recognized by WWE) behind only Ric Flair and John Cena.

themeMusic.name: The Ultimate Warrior
themeMusic.details: Warrior became a two-time WWF Intercontinental Heavyweight Champion and won the WWF World Heavyweight Championship at WrestleMania VI in Toronto, making him the first wrestler to hold both titles concurrently.

themeMusic.name: Umaga
themeMusic.brief: Finisher : Samoan spike Hometown : San Francisco, California
themeMusic.details: He began in the WWE in 2005 as part of the Raw Brand, serving as the enforcer for The McMahons, Vince and Shane

themeMusic.name: The Undertaker
themeMusic.details: The Undertaker started playing basketball after he entered university from high school and in the year 1985, he played basketball for his college team.

themeMusic.name: The USOS
themeMusic.brief: They are sons to former WWE wrestler Rikishi
themeMusic.details: The Usos are members of the renowned Anoa`i family of Samoan wrestlers, which also includes their father Rikishi, uncle Umaga, and cousins Yokozuna and Roman Reigns

themeMusic.name: Vladimir Kozlov
themeMusic.details: He is trained in freestyle wrestling, rugby, football, sambo, kickboxing, judo, jujutsu, Brazilian jiu-jitsu and mixed martial arts.

themeMusic.name: William (Steven) Regal
themeMusic.details: He started wrestling when he was 15 years old. He Worked As A Bricklayer In His Teens for a few weeks
